34
00:02:14,930 --> 00:02:19,090
We don&#39;t know what causes a change in heart rate and blood pressure because we&#39;re getting

35
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:25,349
systematic co-variation between the independent variable and the third confounding variable.

36
00:02:25,349 --> 00:02:29,870
When we use random assignment, that&#39;s not a problem because what was the confounding

37
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:35,830
variable is no longer systematically varying with the independent variable.

